description:
U.S. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth met his counterparts from the Philippines and Indonesia on Friday (October 31), on the sidelines of the ASEAN Defence Summit in Kuala Lumpur.

Hegseth reaffirmed Washingtonâ€™s commitment to its Indo-Pacific allies, warning against Chinaâ€™s â€œcoercionâ€ in the South China Sea, particularly near the Scarborough Shoal.
The U.S. and the Philippines share a mutual defense treaty that includes dozens of annual military drills and access to strategic bases. Washington is also deepening defense cooperation with Indonesia, Thailand, and Malaysia to maintain regional balance and freedom of navigation. China, in response, urged the U.S. to â€œexercise cautionâ€ over Taiwan and reaffirmed its claim to the self-governed island. The meeting comes as tensions rise across the Indo-Pacific, with both Washington and Beijing vying for influence in the region.
